Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1.5 - Interpretation", "Subsection",
 CellFrame->{{0, 0}, {0, 0}},
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982082397998131*^9, 3.982082406449844*^9}, {
  3.982091851370652*^9, 3.982091853995273*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  1, 0.925, 0.925],ExpressionUUID->"a66d18d9-18bb-4066-998d-6939e28fddb6"],

Cell["\<\
- How do the power TF\[CloseCurlyQuote]s depend on homodyne angle and \
com/diff Michelson phases?
- Can we manipulate homodyne angle to detect differential phase?
- Can you think of any more problems we might run into if you actually tried \
to set up a homodyned Michelson?
\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9820917023392687`*^9, 3.982091846796712*^9}, 
   3.9820921844563093`*^9, {3.982141709150285*^9, 3.9821417390659122`*^9}, {
   3.982142242858191*^9, 
   3.982142248059122*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3207abfd-7325-4363-85cf-\
ac984bbe4313"],

Cell["\<\
Used Claude for following plots to hep me wrap my brain around these results \
\
\>", "Text",
